name: glymur
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "0.8.9" %}
package:
  name: glymur
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: Glymur-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.python.org/packages/f2/fd/9eb35de4afe60be4d8bad1dff12cc43c8e03ec822f2ea8889c9586b20989/Glymur-0.8.9.tar.gz
  sha256: ffb1ccdbbb44b245d92474a4898b61c7a6ac5d64d6b18f63d93b8f698c6e1ef9

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt
  entry_points:
    - jp2dump=glymur.command_line:main

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - numpy >=1.7.0
    - lxml >=2.3.2
    - mock
    - contextlib2 >=0.4

  run:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - numpy >=1.7.0
    - lxml >=2.3.2
    - contextlib2 >=0.4
    - openjpeg 2.1.*

test:
  # Python imports
  imports:
    - glymur
    - glymur.data
    - glymur.lib

  commands:
    - python -c "import glymur; j = glymur.Jp2k(glymur.data.nemo()); print(j)"
    - jp2dump --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/quintusdias/glymur
  license: MIT
  summary: 'Tools for accessing JPEG2000 files'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - cadair
    - ehsteve
    - quintusdias
